  "schema:name": "Major and Trace Element Geochemistry of Volcanic Rocks from the Cascadia Subduction Zone",
  "schema:description": "Whole-rock major and trace element geochemical analyses of volcanic rocks collected from Quaternary volcanic centers along the Cascadia subduction zone, Pacific Northwest USA. Samples were collected during field campaigns in 2018-2022 from Mount St. Helens, Mount Adams, Mount Hood, and Crater Lake. Major elements determined by X-ray fluorescence (XRF) spectrometry; trace elements by inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometry (ICP-MS). Data include sample locations, rock classifications, and analytical results with detection limits and measurement uncertainties.",
